# DeployGuard — Komatik HQ Adaptations

> The full HQ protocol lives in `AGENTS.md` (auto-distributed from Komatik hub).
> This file documents only what differs for the DeployGuard repo.

## Branch differences

DeployGuard is a **satellite repo**. The default branch is `main` (not `dev`).

Wherever the HQ prompt says `dev`, substitute `main` for this repo:
- `git log --oneline HEAD..origin/main` (not `origin/dev`)
- `git pull origin main` (not `origin/dev`)
- `git revert <hash> --no-edit && git push origin main` (emergency revert)
- Agent PRs target `main`

There is no `staging` or `master` branch. `main` is the production branch — code pushed here is what the GitHub Action runs.

## Stability check commands (Workflow 4)

DeployGuard's CI pipeline differs from the Komatik monorepo:

```bash
git checkout main && git pull origin main
npm run format:check
npm run lint
npm test
npm run build
git diff --exit-code dist/
```

The `dist/` drift check is critical — `dist/index.js` is the bundled Action runtime that GitHub executes directly.

## Trust levels for this repo

| Agent change | Review level | Why |
| ------------ | ------------ | --- |
| `action.yml` inputs/outputs | Full line-by-line | Contract change — breaks all consumers |
| `src/risk-engine.ts` | Full line-by-line | Shared across Action, MCP, App |
| `src/gate.ts`, `src/main.ts` | Careful review | Core orchestration |
| `src/security.ts`, `src/canary.ts` | Careful review | Security-sensitive modules |
| `dist/index.js` | Verify via build | Never review manually — rebuild and diff |
| `mcp/`, `app/`, `cli/` | Normal review | Separate projects, lower blast radius |
| Docs, README, CHANGELOG | Quick review | High trust |
| Test additions | Quick review | High trust |

## DeployGuard-specific security checks

In addition to the 10-point checklist from the HQ prompt, check:

1. **action.yml parity** — if `src/main.ts` inputs/outputs changed, `action.yml` must match
2. **Fail-open preserved** — gate errors must not block deployments (unless `fail-mode: closed`)
3. **No @actions/\* imports in risk-engine.ts** — this module must stay framework-agnostic for MCP/App sharing
4. **dist/ rebuilt** — any `src/` change requires `npm run build` and committing the new `dist/index.js`
